{
  "text": "and J is the |S| × h all-ones matrix. Since 2-rank(K) = 2, the 2-ranks of A and A ′ differ by at most 2. It is well-known that the 2-rank of any adjacency matrix is even (see [CITATION_1] ), thus we have the following result. Proposition 1.3. Suppose 2-rank(A) = r, then r is even and 2-rank(A ′ ) = r−2, r, or r + 2.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "122269823"
